1. Study Design & Demographics
Study Classification: Repeat Dose Toxicology
Primary Focus: systemic toxicity profile and NOAEL determination
Key Endpoints (prioritized):
  • Clinical pathology (hematology, chemistry, coagulation)
  • Body weights and food consumption
  • Gross and microscopic pathology
  • Organ weights
  • Clinical observations and mortality
Study Type: REPEAT DOSE TOXICITY
Species/Strain: RAT SPRAGUE-DAWLEY
Age: 6-7 WEEKS
Total Animals: 150 (75M / 75F)
Route: ORAL GAVAGE
Dosing Duration: P13W
Recovery: P14D
Period: 2016-01-15 → None
Vehicle Control [Control]: 20 animals (10M/10F)
Vehicle Control with recovery [Control]: 10 animals (5M/5F)
2 mg/kg PCDRUG: 30 animals (15M/15F)
2 mg/kg PCDRUG with recovery: 10 animals (5M/5F)
20 mg/kg PCDRUG [Control]: 30 animals (15M/15F)
20 mg/kg PCDRUG with recovery [Control]: 10 animals (5M/5F)
200 mg/kg PCDRUG [Control]: 30 animals (15M/15F)
200 mg/kg PCDRUG with recovery [Control]: 10 animals (5M/5F)
Available Domains: BG, BW, CL, CO, DD, DM, DS, EG, EX, FW, LB, MA, MI, OM, PC, PM, PP, SC, SE, TA, TE, TF, TS, TX, VS
Available Datasets (from define.xml):
BG: Body Weight Gains • BW: Body Weights • CL: Clinical Observations • CO: Comments • DD: Death Diagnosis • DM: Demographics • DS: Disposition • EG: ECG Test Results • EX: Exposure • FW: Food and Water Consumption • LB: Laboratory Test Results • MA: Macroscopic Findings • MI: Microscopic Findings • OM: Organ Measurements • PC: Pharmacokinetics Concentrations • PM: Palpable Masses • PP: Pharmacokinetics Parameters • SC: Subject Characteristics • SE: Subject Elements • TA: Trial Arms • TE: Trial Elements • TF: Tumor Findings • TS: Trial Summary • TX: Trial Sets • VS: Vital Signs
